On Tue, 16 Feb 1999, Chuck Lever wrote:
> i was also wondering about the use of (ulong) and (void *).  is it true
> that (ulong) is used for physical addresses and void * is used for virtual
> addresses?  wouldn't it be clearer to use a couple of typedefs?
Clearer and safer. Perhaps bus_t, virtual_t, io_t? Though there are some
rumblings about the current scheme being broken for systems with multiple
buses like certain Suns.
